author: Staff Report
title: Big tree history tour of Wilmington set for Friday
text: Big tree history tour of Wilmington set for Friday The Delaware Nature Society is sponsoring the trip which features the largest trees of their kind and historical information about various sites, starting from the Ashland Nature Center in Hockessin. Comment By Staff Report Posted Oct. 19, 2015 @ 12:56 pm The Delaware Nature Society is hosting a "Big Tree and History Tour of Wilmington" this Friday, Oct. 23, from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. The event will start at the Ashland Nature Center, 3511 Barley Mill Road, Hockessin. Participants can tour northern New Castle County to see the largest trees of their kind in Delaware. The tour will include historic properties and other sites around Wilmington to see trees and hear local history. Registration is required. For information, call 239-2334 or see the website delawarenaturesociety.org . The fee is $20 which includes van transportation. Participants should bring a lunch.
